Salesforce, Amgen, Honeywell to become new Dow Average components

Salesforce.com Inc. CRM, -3.52%, Amgen Inc. AMGN, -1.62%, and Honeywell International Inc. HON, -0.62% will become new members of the Dow Jones Industrial Average DJIA, -1.66% by the end of the month, S&P Dow Jones Indices said late Monday. Salesforce will replace Exxon Mobil Corp. XOM, -2.09%, Amgen will replace Pfizer Inc. PFE, -0.77%, and Honey well will replace Raytheon Technologies Corp. RTX, -0.06%, S&P Dow Jones said. "The changes won't disrupt the level of the index," S&P Dow Jones said in a statement. "The divisor used to calculate the index from the components' prices on their respective home exchanges will be changed prior to the opening on August 31, 2020."
